QUESTION 4: Does adding more threads increase the "system load", or is it constant regardless of the number of threads?  Why?
Yes, in this program adding more threads does increase system load because the more of the cpu's resources are being used. However, this is 
only the case when the threads do not have to wait on other things such as IO operations. If they have to wait before they can run this can
lead to the system load being the constant regardless of the thread count.
